Pandas is a Python library used for data manipulation, analysis, and cleaning. It provides powerful data structures like:

DataFrame (like an Excel table)
Series (like a column of data)
Pandas makes working with structured data (tables, CSVs, Excel, databases, etc.) easier and faster!


üîπ Why Use Pandas?
‚úî Easy Data Handling ‚Äì Load, clean, and analyze data quickly.
‚úî Works with CSV, Excel, JSON, SQL, etc. ‚Äì Read & write data from multiple sources.
‚úî Powerful Filtering & Sorting ‚Äì Extract specific data effortlessly.
‚úî Aggregation & Grouping ‚Äì Summarize and analyze large datasets.
‚úî Data Cleaning & Missing Values Handling ‚Äì Handle NaN or incomplete data easily.
‚úî Faster than Excel ‚Äì Handles millions of rows efficiently.
‚úî Works with NumPy & Matplotlib ‚Äì Supports advanced data science and visualization.


import pandas as pd

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ Create a DataFrame
data = {
    'Name': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie', 'David'],
    'Age': [25, 30, 35, 28],
    'City': ['New York', 'Los Angeles', 'Chicago', 'Houston'],
    'Salary': [50000, 60000, 70000, 55000]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
print("\n‚úÖ Original DataFrame:\n", df)

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ Read & Write CSV (Uncomment if needed)
# df.to_csv("output.csv", index=False)
# df = pd.read_csv("output.csv")

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ Select a specific column
print("\n‚úÖ Names Column:\n", df['Name'])

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ Filter rows (People older than 28)
df_filtered = df[df['Age'] > 28]
print("\n‚úÖ Filtered Data (Age > 28):\n", df_filtered)

# 5Ô∏è‚É£ Add a new column
df['Bonus'] = df['Salary'] * 0.10  # 10% of salary
print("\n‚úÖ DataFrame After Adding Bonus:\n", df)

# 6Ô∏è‚É£ Sort by Age
df_sorted = df.sort_values(by='Age')
print("\n‚úÖ Sorted by Age:\n", df_sorted)

# 7Ô∏è‚É£ Group by City and get average Salary
df_grouped = df.groupby('City')['Salary'].mean()
print("\n‚úÖ Average Salary by City:\n", df_grouped)

# 8Ô∏è‚É£ Save the final DataFrame to CSV
df.to_csv("final_output.csv", index=False)
print("\n‚úÖ DataFrame saved to 'final_output.csv'")
